This project uses MJML (Mailjet Markup Language) to build responsive HTML emails.

Key rules:

- All email content must be wrapped in <mjml> > <mj-body> > <mj-section> > <mj-column>
- Use mj-text, mj-button, mj-image, mj-divider, mj-social for content
- Use mj-head with mj-attributes for global styles
- Never use raw <div> or <table> for layout — use MJML components
- Source files live in src/templates/ (.mjml extension); compiled to dist/templates/
- Reusable MJML fragments live in src/blocks/ and are included with <mj-include>; compiled to dist/blocks/ without allowIncludes
- Compiled HTML output goes to dist/ (not committed)
- Run `bun run build` to compile templates and blocks
- Run `bun run build-templates` to compile only templates
- Run `bun run build-blocks` to compile only blocks
- Run `bun run build-watch` to watch templates and blocks
- Run `bun run build-templates-watch` to watch only templates
- Run `bun run build-blocks-watch` to watch only blocks
- Run `bun run build-minify` to compile templates and blocks with minified output
- Run `bun run build-templates-minify` to compile only templates with minified output
- Run `bun run build-blocks-minify` to compile only blocks with minified output
